## Appendix: Country Power Assessments (August 2021)

### United Kingdom Power Assessment

**Overall Empire Score**: 0.27 (Rank: 7 out of 11 major countries)

- **UK is a modest power** in the bottom half of major countries on a flat trajectory
- **Key strength**: strong rule of law/low corruption (Rank: 1)
- **Key weaknesses**: unfavorable economic/financial position, lack of natural resources

#### Economic and Financial Cycles

- **Big cycles look mostly unfavorable** for the UK
- High debt burden: 260% of GDP (non-financial), 106% (government)
- 90% of debt is in UK's own currency (mitigates risk)
- Low expected real growth: 0.9% per year over next 10 years
- Net IIP: -28% of GDP (more foreign debts than assets)
- Limited monetary policy flexibility: short rates at 0.1%, already printing money

#### Internal Order

- **Moderate risk** of internal disorder
- Wealth/income inequality relatively large
- Top 1%/top 10% capture 13%/36% of income (5th and 6th highest among major countries)
- Internal conflict gauge: average (measures protests, political conflict, general discontent)

#### Eight Key Measures of Power

The UK shows no particularly prominent strengths or weaknesses:

- Reserve Currency Status: Weak (Z-score: -0.6, Rank: 4) — getting better
- Markets & Financial Center: Average (Rank: 5) — getting worse
- Cost Competitiveness: Average (Rank: 5) — getting better
- Education: Average (Rank: 6) — getting worse
- Economic Output: Average (Rank: 6) — getting better
- Innovation & Technology: Average (Rank: 7) — getting better
- Trade: Weak (Rank: 7) — getting better
- Military Strength: Average (Rank: 8) — getting better

#### Additional Measures

- Governance/Rule of Law: Strong (Z-score: 1.2, Rank: 1) — getting better
- Resource-Allocation Efficiency: Average (Rank: 4) — getting better
- Character/Determination/Civility: Average (Rank: 7) — getting worse
- Infrastructure & Investment: Weak (Rank: 10) — getting worse
- Geology: Weak (Rank: 10) — getting better
- Acts of Nature: Average (Rank: 4)

